trans-unit.source: Specifies how to handle values that are missing from a dataset
trans-unit.target: Specifies how to handle values that are missing from a dataset

trans-unit.source: The <ui>Missing Values Scrubber</ui> module provides some basic methods for handling missing values.
trans-unit.target: The <ui>Missing Values Scrubber</ui> module provides some basic methods for handling missing values.

trans-unit.source: It expects a dataset as input, and it returns a dataset with missing values that are substituted by a method that you select.
trans-unit.target: It expects a dataset as input, and it returns a dataset with missing values that are substituted by a method that you select.

trans-unit.source: This module is provided for backward compatibility with experiments created using the pre-release version of Azure Machine Learning Studio, and will soon be deprecated.
trans-unit.target: This module is provided for backward compatibility with experiments created using the pre-release version of Azure Machine Learning Studio, and will soon be deprecated.

trans-unit.source: We recommend that you modify your experiments to use <link xlink:href="d2c5ca2f-7323-41a3-9b7e-da917c99f0c4" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Clean Missing Data</link> instead.
trans-unit.target: We recommend that you modify your experiments to use <link xlink:href="d2c5ca2f-7323-41a3-9b7e-da917c99f0c4" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Clean Missing Data</link> instead.

trans-unit.source: How to Use Missing Values Scrubber
trans-unit.target: How to Use Missing Values Scrubber

trans-unit.source: There are multiple ways to handle missing values.
trans-unit.target: There are multiple ways to handle missing values.

trans-unit.source: However, whichever method you choose, it applies to the entire set of columns you have selected.
trans-unit.target: However, whichever method you choose, it applies to the entire set of columns you have selected.

trans-unit.source: If you need to treat missing values differently in some columns, use <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project columns</link> to select a subset of data before applying <ui>Missing Values Scrubber</ui>.
trans-unit.target: If you need to treat missing values differently in some columns, use <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project columns</link> to select a subset of data before applying <ui>Missing Values Scrubber</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Use this drop-down list to select which method to use to handle missing values.
trans-unit.target: Use this drop-down list to select which method to use to handle missing values.

trans-unit.source: This is only needed if you choose to substitute missing values with a custom value.
trans-unit.target: This is only needed if you choose to substitute missing values with a custom value.

trans-unit.source: If you specify a floating-point value to replace missing values in a column of integers, the value substituted for the missing value will be this value converted to the nearest integer.
trans-unit.target: If you specify a floating-point value to replace missing values in a column of integers, the value substituted for the missing value will be this value converted to the nearest integer.

trans-unit.source: Choose whether to keep or remove columns with all values missing.
trans-unit.target: Choose whether to keep or remove columns with all values missing.

trans-unit.source: Choose whether to generate missing value indicator columns.
trans-unit.target: Choose whether to generate missing value indicator columns.

trans-unit.source: You can select from the following substitution methods to replace missing values:
trans-unit.target: You can select from the following substitution methods to replace missing values:

trans-unit.source: Replaces missing values by using "Multiple Imputation by Chained Equations" (MICE), a method broadly used in the statistics literature since work by Donald Rubin in the 1970s.
trans-unit.target: Replaces missing values by using "Multiple Imputation by Chained Equations" (MICE), a method broadly used in the statistics literature since work by Donald Rubin in the 1970s.

trans-unit.source: This method initializes the missing entries with a default value.
trans-unit.target: This method initializes the missing entries with a default value.

trans-unit.source: Then it updates each column by using an appropriate regression or classification algorithm.
trans-unit.target: Then it updates each column by using an appropriate regression or classification algorithm.

trans-unit.source: These updates are repeated a number of times, as specified by the Number of Iterations parameter.
trans-unit.target: These updates are repeated a number of times, as specified by the Number of Iterations parameter.

trans-unit.source: Assigns the replacement value to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, Boolean, or Date.
trans-unit.target: Assigns the replacement value to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, Boolean, or Date.

trans-unit.source: For date columns, the replacement value can also be entered as the number of 100-nanosecond ticks since 1/1/0001 12:00 AM.
trans-unit.target: For date columns, the replacement value can also be entered as the number of 100-nanosecond ticks since 1/1/0001 12:00 AM.

trans-unit.source: Assigns the replacement value to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, or Boolean
trans-unit.target: Assigns the replacement value to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, or Boolean

trans-unit.source: Assigns the median of a column to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer or Double.
trans-unit.target: Assigns the median of a column to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer or Double.

trans-unit.source: Assigns the mode of a column to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, Boolean, or Categorical.
trans-unit.target: Assigns the mode of a column to any missing value in every column with a data type of Integer, Double, Boolean, or Categorical.

trans-unit.source: Removes all rows in the dataset with one or more missing values.
trans-unit.target: Removes all rows in the dataset with one or more missing values.

trans-unit.source: This is useful if the missing value can be considered as missing at random.
trans-unit.target: This is useful if the missing value can be considered as missing at random.

trans-unit.source: Replaces the missing values by using a linear model that analyzes the correlations between the columns and estimates a low-dimensional approximation of the data, from which the full data is reconstructed.
trans-unit.target: Replaces the missing values by using a linear model that analyzes the correlations between the columns and estimates a low-dimensional approximation of the data, from which the full data is reconstructed.

trans-unit.source: The underlying dimensionality reduction is a probabilistic form of Principal Component Analysis (PCA).
trans-unit.target: The underlying dimensionality reduction is a probabilistic form of Principal Component Analysis (PCA).

trans-unit.source: It implements a variant of the model proposed in the Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series B 21(3), 611–622 by Tipping and Bishop.
trans-unit.target: It implements a variant of the model proposed in the Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series B 21(3), 611–622 by Tipping and Bishop.

trans-unit.source: Compared to other options (such as MICE), this option has the advantage of not requiring the application of predictors for each column.
trans-unit.target: Compared to other options (such as MICE), this option has the advantage of not requiring the application of predictors for each column.

trans-unit.source: Instead, it immediately approximates the covariance of the full dataset.
trans-unit.target: Instead, it immediately approximates the covariance of the full dataset.

trans-unit.source: It may therefore offer a better performance for datasets that have missing values in many columns.
trans-unit.target: It may therefore offer a better performance for datasets that have missing values in many columns.

trans-unit.source: The key limitations of this method are:
trans-unit.target: The key limitations of this method are:

trans-unit.source: It expands categorical columns into numerical indicators and computes a dense covariance matrix of the resulting data.
trans-unit.target: It expands categorical columns into numerical indicators and computes a dense covariance matrix of the resulting data.

trans-unit.source: It is not optimized for sparse representations.
trans-unit.target: It is not optimized for sparse representations.

trans-unit.source: For these reasons, datasets with large numbers of columns and/or large categorical domains (tens of thousands) are not supported due to prohibitive space consumption.
trans-unit.target: For these reasons, datasets with large numbers of columns and/or large categorical domains (tens of thousands) are not supported due to prohibitive space consumption.
